title: Spider-Man, why did you create that guy? | Spider-Man: Across the Spider-verse #shorts #spiderman
description:
In this video, The Spot (Dr. Jonathan Ohnn/Dalmatian/Cow/Jason Schwartzman) tells Miles Morales (Shameik Moore) that he created him while Miles created him. Jefferson Davis, Mile's father, then asks, "Spider-Man, why did you create that guy?" (why Miles Morales, or Spider-Man,  created The Spot).


SPOILERS DOWN BELOW!





he Spot is an Alchemax scientist whose body was infused with portals after the Alchemax collider explosion that was caused by the fight between Miles Morales and Kingpin in Spider-Man: Into the Spider-verse. Blaming Miles for his dilemma, the Spot brings Miles to Alchemax and reveals that the spider that bit Miles came from another universe when the Spot was testing the collider. 

He then accidentally transports himself into a void, where he learns to travel to other universes containing the Alchemax collider to use them to empower himself. He hates Miles Morales for what he did because no one will hire the Spot because of how he looks and the fact that he cannot control his powers. 

That's why he proceeds to do petty crimes such as stealing an ATM with his newfound powers. Also, in Spider-Man: Into the Spider-verse, when Peter B. Parker and Miles Morales escape Alchemax after stealing data to create a new drive to stop the collider created by Kingpin in hopes of finding his wife and son again. They run away from Dr. Olivia Octavius and other Alchemax scientists, in which Miles throws a bagel behind them to slow down their pursuers. This resulted in The Spot (Dr. Jonathan Ohnn) being hit in the head by the bagel, further increasing his hatred for Miles Morales and Spider-Man in general.

he Spot is an Alchemax scientist whose body was infused with portals after the Alchemax collider explosion that was caused by the fight between Miles Morales and Kingpin in Spider-Man: Into the Spider-verse. They run away from Dr. Olivia Octavius and other Alchemax scientists, in which Miles throws a bagel behind them to slow down their pursuers. This resulted in The Spot (Dr. Jonathan Ohnn) being hit in the head by the bagel, further increasing his hatred for Miles Morales and Spider-Man in general.

Parker (Jake Johnson) tells Miles Morales that his ability to go invisible and use venom blasts is unique to him compared to every other Spider-Man in the Spider-verse. Now, they need to escape Alchemax Labs and use the Alchemax data to return to their respective dimensions.


SPOILERS DOWN BELOW!




After Miles Morales makes a lot of noise from falling through the ceiling, Dr. Olivia Octavius (Kathryn Hahn) catches Miles Morales and Peter B. Parker in the act of attempting to steal Alchemax data to stop the super-collider created by Kingpin (Liev Schreiber), which prevents many different Spider-Man from going back to their original dimension. Miles Morales goes invisible right as Dr. Olivia Octavius (or Doc Ock) walks through the door, leading to Peter B. Parker distracting her while Miles hacks her Alchemax computer in order to steal the data for the USB drive they need to put a stop to Kingpin's plans.

Miguel O'Hara attempts to stop Miles Morales from escaping the Spider-verse due to the fact that Miles is trying to break the canon timeline among the different types of Spider-Man. (trying to save his father, Jefferson Davis, from being killed by The Spot, a canon event in his timeline)
